                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440610-1797-offence-1 t18440610-name-1409"></join>Henry Gower</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1410" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1410" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1410" type="surname" value="GOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1410" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY GOWER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at Barnes. The prisoner lodged in my house—I</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184406100212"></xptr>
               <p>lost this shawl—the prisoner came to me—I charged her with having stolen it—she denied it—I said it was no use to deny it, for I had found out where it was pledged in her name—I had been to Putney and seen it—I did not say it would be better for her to tell.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1411" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1411" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1411" type="surname" value="GOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1411" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN GOWER</persName>
                  </hi>. This is my husband's shawl—I saw it safe at home on the 20th of May.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1412" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1412" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1412" type="surname" value="SPENCER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1412" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE SPENCER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a pawnbroker. I produce this shawl, which I took in of Stowell—she was alone when she pledged it—the bill against her was thrown out—this is the duplicate I gave of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1413" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1413" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1413" type="surname" value="CANNON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1413" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN CANNON</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable V</hi> 201.) I produce this duplicate, which I found at Stowell's house—I took the prisoner for taking the shawl—she asked me to allow her to dress, which I did—I sat down in the room—she said, "In taking this shawl I have added more to my misfortune."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CLARKSON</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Is this your writing to this deposition? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; I was asked if it was correct, and I said it was—(<hi rend="italic">read—</hi>" It only added to her misfortune in having anything to do with the shawl")—she said it added to her misfortune in taking the shawl.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-1414" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1414" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1414" type="surname" value="GOWER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-1414" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY GOWER</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined. Q.</hi> Did you in any way tell her that it would be better for her, or for her advantage, if she would tell you the truth and confess? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Will you take your oath you did not say it would be better she should tell you who took it, as you had found out where it was pledged, and in her name? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Some of those words I did not—I said it was no use to deny it, I had found out where it was pledged.</p>
